als for bodying beyond current legal and political limits into enchantingly vibrant and ecosomatically alive futures.  afunded by Deutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 4aAliveness. 4aBody. 4aBusiness Ethics. 4aCultural Anthropology. 4aEcology. 4aEconomy. 4aEcosomatics. 4aEthnology. 4aFascia. 4aGabon. 4aSocial Relations. 4aSomatics. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAliveness.  aBody.  aBusiness Ethics.  aCultural Anthropology.  aEcology.  aEconomy.  aEcosomatics.  aEthnology.  aFascia.  aGabon.  aSocial Relations.  aSomatics.2 aDeutsche Forschungsgemeinschaft (DFG)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z978311076731540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839460115zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839460115423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839460115/original  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK